Interview Answer
ApplicationSet is an ArgoCD controller that dynamically generates and manages multiple ArgoCD Applications from a single template. It is commonly used for multi-environment, multi-cluster, and large-scale microservice deployments, reducing the need to create and maintain individual Application resources manually.

In large enterprises using EKS and GitOps, ApplicationSets are often used to manage dozens or hundreds of applications across multiple clusters and environments from a single declarative configuration.
